    "transliteration": "This day is dedicated to the Imams Musa ibn Ja’far al-Kazim, Ali ibn Musa al-Rida, Muhammad ibn Ali al-Taqi al-Jawad, and Ali ibn Muhammad al-Naqi al-Hadi - peace be upon them all. their Ziyarah on Wednesdays is as follows:\r\n\r\nBISMILLAHIR RAHMANIR RAHEEM ASSALAAMO A'LAYKUM YAA AWLEYAAA-AL LAAHE ASSALAAMO A'LAYKUM YAA HOJAJAL LAAHE ASSALAAMO A'LAYKUM YAA NOORAL LAAHE FEE ZOLOMAATIL ARZE ASSALAAMO A'LAYKUM SALAWAATUL LAAHE A'LAYKUM WA A'LAA AALE BAYTEKOMUT TAYYEBEENAT TAAHEREENA BE ABEE ANTUM WA UMMEE LAQAD A'BADTOMUL LAAHA MUKHLESEENA WA JAAHAD-TUM FIL LAAHE HAQQA JEHAADEHEE HATTAA ATAAKOMUL YAQEENO FA LA-A'NAL LAAHO AA'DAAA-AKUM MENAL JINNE WAL INSE AJMA-E'EN WA ANAA ABRA-O ELAL LAAHE WA ELAYKUM MINHUM YAA MAWLAAYA YAA ABAA IBRAAHEEMA MOOSABNA JAA'FAR YAA MAWLAAYA YAA ABAL HASANE A'LIY YABNA MOOSAA YAA MAWLAAYA YAA ABAA JA'FARE MOHAMMAD ABNA A'LIYYE YAA MAWLAAYA YAA ABAL HASANE A'LIY YABNA MOHAMMADIN ANAA MAWLAN LAKUM MOMENUN BE SIRREKUM WA JAHREKUM MOTAZAY YEFUN BEKUM FEE YAWMEKUM HAAZAA WA HOWA YAWMUL ARBA-A'A-E WA MUSTAJEERUN BEKUM FA AZEEFOONEE WA AJEEROONEE BE AALE BAYTEKOMUT TAYYEBEENAT TAAHEREENA.", 
    "english": "This day is dedicated to the Imams Musa ibn Ja’far al-Kazim, Ali ibn Musa al-Rida, Muhammad ibn Ali al-Taqi al-Jawad, and Ali ibn Muhammad al-Naqi al-Hadi - peace be upon them all. their Ziyarah on Wednesdays is as follows:\r\n\r\nPeace be upon you [all], O saints of Allah! Peace be upon you, O arguments of Allah! Peace be upon you, O light of Allah in the darkness of the earth! Peace be upon you. Blessings of Allah be upon you and upon your Household, the pure and immaculate. May Allah accept my father and mother as ransoms for you! Indeed, you worshipped Allah sincerely and strove for His sake with due strife until death came upon you. So, may Allah curse all your enemies from the jinn and human beings. And I release myself before Allah and before you from them (i.e. your enemies). O my master, O Abu- Ibrahim, Musa, the son of Ja'far! O my master, O Abu’l- Hasan, 'AIT, the son of Musa! O my master, O Abu- Ja'far, Muhammad, the son of 'AH! O my master, O Abu’l- Hasan, 'Ali, the son of Muhammad! I am your servant, I believe in your secret and open affairs, and I am staying with you as your guest, on this day, which is Wednesday, and I am in your vicinity; so, receive me as your guest and neighbor, [I ask you] by your Household, the pure and immaculate. "
